VBalamurali Krishna a young seasoned artiste from Chennai performed on the second day of the Sri Lakshmi Nrisimha Swamy Seva Samithi&#8217;s musical fest.His group consist of Dinakar on violin, Aravind on mridangam, Nemani on ghatam and Shyam on kanjeera. Balamurali is a disciple of P.S. Narayana Swamy. He began his recital withBegada Varnam. He has a rich voice and also a good laya, Murali has shown lot of improvement in his style as he is now coming out withmanodharma.Siddivinayakamin Shanmukha Priya was the next to come with flowingswaram.Endaro Mahanubhavuluin Sree Ragam of Thyagaraja was neatly sung.The highlight of the concert wasPanthuvaraliwhich Balamurali sang very competently with all the majorsancharasreflecting in it. Thyagaraja&#8217;sAparama Bhakthiwith neraval at its best was finely displayed.Narasimha Mamavain Arabhi was another attraction of the day.Needayaradhain Vasantha Bhairavi was a fast number.The artiste sung with ease. The main attraction was Khambhoji and Murali did well to maintain the essence of theragam.O Ranga Saiof Thyagaraja was taken up with neraval atBhoo lolka Vaibhavamuwas nice with breezyswaramin it. Dinakar&#8217;s support on the violin was laudable.He enhanced theragameffect by his good anticipation. Aravind on the mridangam did well in his accompaniment.Histanialong with Nemani on the ghatam and Shyam on the kanjeera was enjoyable.
